  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted covering parametric sweeps of impeller clearance and rotational speed; results are narrated in the validation records. The UQ campaign included one-at-a-time sensitivity sweeps across five operating points, confirming monotonic hemolysis response to flow rate and corroborating the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across the design space.",
